  <datafield tag="856" ind1="4" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="u">http://inspirehep.net/record/1245955/files/icrc2013-0805-01.png</subfield>
    <subfield code="y">00000 The VERITAS ($>$350 GeV daily integrations, top), Fermi-LAT (0.3-300 GeV, middle), and Swift-$\textit{XRT}$ (0.3-10 keV, bottom) light curves for LS I +61$^{\circ}$ 303 during December 2011 - February 2012. The data is also shown as a function of orbital phase ($\phi$). VERITAS 99$\%$ and $Fermi$-LAT 90$\%$ flux upper limits are represented by arrows. The grey shaded regions represent the observations obtained simultaneously which are used for the X-ray/TeV correlation studies in this work.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="856" ind1="4" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="u">http://inspirehep.net/record/1245955/files/icrc2013-0805-02.png</subfield>
    <subfield code="y">00001 The spectral energy distribution of LS I +61$^{\circ}$ 303 derived from contemporaneous $Fermi$-LAT and VERITAS observations in 2011/2012 showing a clear gap in emission between $\sim$4 GeV and 300 GeV.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="856" ind1="4" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="u">http://inspirehep.net/record/1245955/files/icrc2013-0805-03.png</subfield>
    <subfield code="y">00002 The strictly simultaneous TeV/X-ray observations taken on LS I$^{\circ}$. Filled circles represent data from this work and the open squares represent observations detailed in \cite{bib:USLSI3} and references therein. The total correlation between the flux in each band is 0.36$\pm$0.32, consistent with two uncorrelated datasets.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="856" ind1="4" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="u">http://inspirehep.net/record/1245955/files/icrc2013-0805-04.png</subfield>
    <subfield code="y">00003 The phase folded TeV light curve of HESS J0632+057 (color points) from VERITAS (squares and triangles), HESS (filled circles), and MAGIC (open circles). The $Swift$-XRT light curve points are also plotted as grey points. The periodicity in the source is clearly evident in both TeV and X-ray energies.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="856" ind1="4" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="u">http://inspirehep.net/record/1245955/files/icrc2013-0805-05.png</subfield>
    <subfield code="y">00004 The differential energy spectrum from VERITAS, HESS, and MAGIC TeV observations taken from phases 0.2-0.4 only. The source is remarkably stable during its active phases, showing only variations in the flux normalization.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="856" ind1="4" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="u">http://inspirehep.net/record/1245955/files/icrc2013-0805-06.png</subfield>
    <subfield code="y">00005 The relative orbital distances of the known TeV binaries in astronomical units. The orbits are shown without respect to inclination or viewing angle. Distances derived from \cite{bib:CasaresJ0632, bib:Aragona2009, bib:ISusch}. The colored line represent regions of higher and lower TeV activity from the systems.</subfield>
  </datafield>
